Dead zones traditionally exist so if a controller has a tweak on their stick, their character may

75
00:04:33,973 --> 00:04:38,598
drift. So to keep the sticks from drifting, you have this dead zone saying that if it's

76
00:04:38,598 --> 00:04:41,521
within this area of the controller, ignore the input.

77
00:04:42,133 --> 00:04:48,396
Now, having this be custom helps people with mobility issues too, because it allows them to

78
00:04:48,396 --> 00:04:53,279
say if I have hand jitter or something, it allows them to go through and say, okay, so I only want

79
00:04:53,279 --> 00:04:58,521
to worry about the edges, ignore any time my hand shakes, I just care if it's full throttle or

80
00:04:58,521 --> 00:05:05,245
nothing. This lets them be more able to do this. At the same point in time, this is Borderlands 3

81
00:05:05,245 --> 00:05:05,645
Scream.

82
00:05:06,336 --> 00:05:09,639
