83
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:11,661
That means that if you have something

84
00:05:11,661 --> 00:05:13,322
where you want to bias it,

85
00:05:13,322 --> 00:05:16,685
so up, down, left, right on a stick is most of it,

86
00:05:16,685 --> 00:05:18,186
and diagonals are mostly ignored,

87
00:05:18,186 --> 00:05:19,928
they're shifted to the edge,

88
00:05:19,928 --> 00:05:21,009
it allows you to do that.

89
00:05:21,009 --> 00:05:23,070
So if you just want to be able to look up and down

90
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:23,991
or left and right,

91
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:27,214
and you keep having your controller drift in various ways,

92
00:05:27,214 --> 00:05:29,876
this gives you more options to do that.

93
00:05:29,876 --> 00:05:31,458
And I love that that exists.

94
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:36,791
Analog sensitivity fits multiple needs.

95
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:39,794
It needs to be faster for those who have trouble

96
00:05:39,794 --> 00:05:42,737
