262
00:15:05,315 --> 00:15:06,936
It doesn't matter.

263
00:15:06,936 --> 00:15:10,237
It's about having an experience.

264
00:15:10,237 --> 00:15:13,479
Now, optional haptic feedback is important to me

265
00:15:13,479 --> 00:15:15,500
in particular because it makes my hands go numb.

266
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:20,475
The more vibrations there are to a device,

267
00:15:20,475 --> 00:15:22,358
the harder time I'm going to have playing.

268
00:15:22,358 --> 00:15:26,263
So it's really important to me to be able to turn that off.

269
00:15:26,263 --> 00:15:28,525
When I was playing Sea of Solitude, as you see here,

270
00:15:28,525 --> 00:15:32,090
the menu, the main menu, has to control your vibrations.

271
00:15:32,517 --> 00:15:34,918
And I'm like, no, my hands are already going numb.

272
00:15:34,918 --> 00:15:37,279
I immediately went to the menu and I was able to turn it off.

273
00:15:37,279 --> 00:15:39,880
The thing is it actually had multiple levels of it.

274
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:43,381
So I could say I want maximum controller vibrations,

275
00:15:43,381 --> 00:15:45,442
or I could say I just want the things

276
00:15:45,442 --> 00:15:49,043
that are really important and all the, you know,

277
00:15:49,043 --> 00:15:51,264
environmental stuff, I don't care as much.

278
00:15:51,264 --> 00:15:52,064
Or I can say none.

279
00:15:52,064 --> 00:15:53,085
I immediately said none,

280
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:57,826
but I really deeply appreciate that they had multiple levels.

281
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:00,908
And I also would love to see things like,

282
00:16:00,908 --> 00:16:04,690
really vibrations could have tracks like audio has tracks.

283
00:16:04,690 --> 00:16:08,511
So like when you have the environmental sounds

284
00:16:08,511 --> 00:16:12,993
and you have music things or special effects,

285
00:16:12,993 --> 00:16:14,194
you could do the same thing with haptic.

286
00:16:15,074 --> 00:16:20,458
And the fact that you can turn on and off things is wonderful because that means that if it's

287
00:16:20,458 --> 00:16:26,241
something that cues in on like, oh, there's a special key in the room, I might still be able

288
00:16:26,241 --> 00:16:32,365
to feel that. But at the same point in time, I don't necessarily need to hit every single time

289
00:16:32,365 --> 00:16:39,209
a bomb drops. I don't need my controller vibrating. So I love the fact that these exist. It helps so

290
00:16:39,209 --> 00:16:39,510
much.

291
00:16:42,551 --> 00:16:46,233
Provide as many difficulty options as possible.

292
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:47,974
Easy mode is okay.

293
00:16:47,974 --> 00:16:51,096
And really, easy varies for everyone.

294
00:16:51,096 --> 00:16:52,197
When it's easy for one person,

295
00:16:52,197 --> 00:16:54,238
could be impossible for someone else,

296
00:16:54,238 --> 00:16:56,279
and we should not be policing experiences.

297
00:16:56,279 --> 00:16:59,281
The most important point is to have an experience.

298
00:17:01,165 --> 00:17:04,187
